OL,6,F Ted Chamberlain met the students and
OL,7,Fresidents taking part in the Reading
OL,8,FFriends initiative in ScissettJTwo
OL,9,Fgenerations have been forging unlikely
OL,10,Ffriendships at a care home near
OL,11,FHuddersfield through a scheme aimed at
OL,12,Ftackling loneliness among older
OL,13,Fpeople.JA group of students from
OL,14,FShelley College have been spending
OL,15,Fregular time at nearby Scissett Mount
OL,16,FCare Home, taking part in the Reading
OL,17,FFriends initiative, where youngsters
OL,18,Fread and chat with residents.JResearch
OL,19,Ffrom Age UK says there more than two
OL,20,Fmillion over-75s in England live
OL,21,Falone. More than a million older
OL,22,Fpeople say they go more than a month
OL,23,Fwithout speaking to a friend,
OL,24,Fneighbour or relative.
