OL,6,F"It is really nice to talk because
OL,7,Fobviously you are younger and they are
OL,8,Folder but you are able to talk, you
OL,9,Fare able to have a conversation and
OL,10,Fjust discuss different things that
OL,11,Fmaybe you would not talk to someone
OL,12,Fyour age about."JAnother student, Evie
OL,13,FHart, said: "I did not think it would
OL,14,Fbe this open. I thought it might be a
OL,15,Fbit more closed off and they might not
OL,16,Fwant to speak as much but they have
OL,17,Fall been very open. It has been nice.
OL,18,FI have enjoyed it."JTwo of the care
OL,19,Fhome residents, Diane Newton and Joan
OL,20,FSkidmore, praised the students for
OL,21,Ftheir kindness and said the scheme was
OL,22,Fhelping them have fun.
